{{Quote|What is the good, if not the teacher of the bad? What is the bad, if not the task of the good?|The Question of Master Jrul|<ref name="Revenge of the Sith novel">[[Star Wars: Revenge of the Sith (novelization)|''Star Wars'': Episode III ''Revenge of the Sith'' novelization]]</ref>}}
The '''Question of Master Jrul''' was a famous bit of philosophy from [[Jedi Master/Legends|Jedi Master]] [[Jrul]], formulated some time before the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]]. The Master's question pondered the connection between good and evil. Fellow [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] Master [[Obi-Wan Kenobi/Legends|Obi-Wan Kenobi]] remembered this question during the [[Battle of Coruscant/Legends|Battle of Coruscant]]<ref name="Revenge of the Sith novel" /> in [[19 BBY/Legends|19 BBY]]<ref name="TNEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref> while facing the [[Supreme Commander of the Droid Armies/Legends|Separatist Supreme Commander]], [[Grievous/Legends|Grievous]].<ref name="Revenge of the Sith novel" />

==Behind the scenes==
The Question of Master Jrul was first mentioned in the [[2005]] novel [[Star Wars: Revenge of the Sith (novelization)|''Star Wars Episode III: Revenge of the Sith'']] written by [[Matthew Stover]].<ref name="Revenge of the Sith novel" />

